      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Economic studies offer mixed results, so there isn't a single consensus. Some research suggests that higher wages boost local consumer spending, which can benefit small businesses. Conversely, other studies indicate that increased labor costs can force small, low-margin operations to cut jobs or raise prices, potentially slowing local growth. The net effect often depends on the specific local economy and how businesses adapt to the wage change.",
